There is also the fatal part played by the gentle Anna in hastening the catastrophe : it is she who induces Dido to yield to her love, and who prepares the pyre for her sister's death3 and she has to endure the reproaches and jealousy of Dido, and to perform the thankless task of trying to make Aeneas relent.
